1
00:00:00,967 --> 00:00:02,033
<i>Looks like someone
got here before us.</i>

2
00:00:02,300 --> 00:00:04,067
<i> This is Sir Magnus's car.</i>

3
00:00:04,067 --> 00:00:07,167
<i>I cannot believe
that all this time,</i>

4
00:00:07,167 --> 00:00:10,067
<i>we risked our lives
because of you, Greta.</i>

5
00:00:10,067 --> 00:00:12,333
<i>No matter what happens,
you are still my mother.</i>

6
00:00:12,333 --> 00:00:14,667
<i>But, Ma, if you really
love us,</i>

7
00:00:14,667 --> 00:00:16,333
<i> you'll do what's right.</i>

8
00:00:16,333 --> 00:00:18,200
<i>Please, Greta,
come with us.</i>

9
00:00:18,200 --> 00:00:19,667
<i> I can't handle it.</i>

10
00:00:20,300 --> 00:00:22,167
<i>I put up with it
for 10 years.</i>

11
00:00:22,167 --> 00:00:23,567
<i> You can do it too.</i>

12
00:00:24,167 --> 00:00:25,367
<i> Please.</i>

13
00:00:25,367 --> 00:00:26,500
<i> "Please"?</i>

14
00:00:28,100 --> 00:00:30,533
<i>- That's enough!
- That's for my father!</i>

15
00:00:30,533 --> 00:00:31,433
<i> Greta.</i>

16
00:00:33,167 --> 00:00:34,567
<i> It's my fault too.</i>

17
00:00:34,600 --> 00:00:36,667
<i>I wasn't a very good
husband to her.</i>

18
00:00:36,667 --> 00:00:39,667
<i>Greta has no one
to blame but herself.</i>

19
00:00:39,667 --> 00:00:41,733
<i> She can't run away this time.</i>

20
00:00:41,733 --> 00:00:43,200
<i> A lot of people died.</i>

21
00:00:43,200 --> 00:00:45,233
<i>How did you know
about this resthouse?</i>

22
00:00:45,233 --> 00:00:47,100
<i> I've been here before</i>

23
00:00:47,100 --> 00:00:51,367
<i>when I drove Sir Magnus
and Ayen here.</i>

24
00:00:51,367 --> 00:00:52,367
<i> Sorry, dude.</i>

25
00:00:53,267 --> 00:00:54,233
<i> It's okay.</i>

26
00:00:55,133 --> 00:00:56,067
<i> It's in the past.</i>

27
00:00:56,433 --> 00:00:59,267
<i> Emil Padua, stop pretending.</i>

28
00:00:59,267 --> 00:01:01,067
<i> Your case will only get worse.</i>

29
00:01:01,067 --> 00:01:03,200
<i> Your doctor is very good.</i>

30
00:01:03,200 --> 00:01:05,400
<i> Young but skilled.</i>

31
00:01:05,400 --> 00:01:07,433
<i>You will be transferred
to our custody.</i>

32
00:01:07,467 --> 00:01:09,067
<i> We'll talk there.</i>

33
00:01:09,067 --> 00:01:11,633
<i>You know Greta.
She's not as tough as you.</i>

34
00:01:11,633 --> 00:01:13,800
<i> I don't know if you've heard,</i>

35
00:01:13,800 --> 00:01:15,567
<i>but she attempted suicide
before.</i>

36
00:01:20,800 --> 00:01:23,300
- [GRETA SOBBING]
- Ma?

37
00:01:23,300 --> 00:01:24,300
Ma!

38
00:01:24,667 --> 00:01:25,533
Ma!

39
00:01:26,267 --> 00:01:27,333
Ma, open the door!

40
00:01:28,633 --> 00:01:30,267
- [LIAM] Ma!
- [BANGING ON DOOR]

41
00:01:30,267 --> 00:01:32,233
- [SOBBING]
- Open the door, Ma!

42
00:01:32,233 --> 00:01:35,433
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

43
00:01:35,433 --> 00:01:36,700
[LIAM] Ma, I'm coming in!

44
00:01:37,733 --> 00:01:39,533
- Ma!
- [BANGING ON DOOR]

45
00:01:41,300 --> 00:01:42,467
Ma!

46
00:01:44,500 --> 00:01:45,633
[GRUNTS]

47
00:01:46,367 --> 00:01:53,100
- [GRETA SOBBING]
- [SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

48
00:01:53,100 --> 00:01:54,500
I'm sorry...

49
00:01:55,233 --> 00:01:57,200
I'm sorry, Liam.

50
00:01:57,800 --> 00:02:00,167
[SOBBING]

51
00:02:00,167 --> 00:02:02,433
I'll face everything.

52
00:02:03,800 --> 00:02:06,100
I'll face everything.

53
00:02:06,767 --> 00:02:13,633
- [SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [GRETA SOBBING]

54
00:02:22,267 --> 00:02:29,167
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

55
00:03:07,333 --> 00:03:08,500
[TELEPHONE RINGING]

56
00:03:08,500 --> 00:03:09,500
Hi, doc.

57
00:03:11,433 --> 00:03:13,700
Wow, you really came to visit.

58
00:03:14,633 --> 00:03:15,767
Visit?

59
00:03:16,600 --> 00:03:19,767
Uh... let me remind you,
I'm from Alicante.

60
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:23,433
It's my sister's birthday,
and we ordered pizza.

61
00:03:23,467 --> 00:03:25,500
I brought you the leftovers.

62
00:03:25,500 --> 00:03:31,267
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

63
00:03:36,267 --> 00:03:38,800
It's still whole,
and it's my favorite.

64
00:03:39,733 --> 00:03:41,933
What's with your smile?
You don't want it? Give it--

65
00:03:41,933 --> 00:03:43,567
Of course, I want it.

66
00:03:43,567 --> 00:03:46,767
I-I'll share it with the other
nurses and doctors.

67
00:03:46,767 --> 00:03:47,800
Thank you.

68
00:03:49,233 --> 00:03:50,700
I didn't know you smile a lot.

69
00:03:50,700 --> 00:03:55,600
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

70
00:03:55,633 --> 00:03:58,233
- [CHUCKLES SOFTLY]
- [PHONE RINGING]

71
00:03:58,233 --> 00:04:00,367
Hold on, someone's calling me.

72
00:04:03,633 --> 00:04:04,633
Oh.

73
00:04:05,367 --> 00:04:08,600
Hey, Shiela. What is it?

74
00:04:09,300 --> 00:04:11,967
[SHIELA]<i> Luna, what time
</i> are you coming home?

75
00:04:11,967 --> 00:04:15,433
Later. I'll call you
when I'm on my way home, okay?

76
00:04:16,233 --> 00:04:17,267
Don't worry.

77
00:04:17,967 --> 00:04:19,400
Happy birthday.

78
00:04:19,767 --> 00:04:21,333
Thank you for the pizza!

79
00:04:21,867 --> 00:04:25,200
Luna, is he the doctor
you were talking about?

80
00:04:25,733 --> 00:04:29,533
Doc, thank you
for saving my sister's life.

81
00:04:29,567 --> 00:04:33,367
Luna, you were right.
Doc's handsome.

82
00:04:33,367 --> 00:04:34,900
<i>No wonder you've
got a crush on him.</i>

83
00:04:34,900 --> 00:04:36,633
Okay, bye, Shiela. Take care.

84
00:04:37,467 --> 00:04:40,033
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

85
00:04:40,033 --> 00:04:42,767
Uh... I'll get going now, doc.

86
00:04:42,767 --> 00:04:43,733
Bye!

87
00:04:44,933 --> 00:04:46,233
Hey, wait a minute!

88
00:04:46,833 --> 00:04:47,767
Huh?

89
00:04:47,767 --> 00:04:49,333
There's something
I need to tell you.

90
00:04:49,333 --> 00:04:50,667
What is it?

91
00:04:50,867 --> 00:04:54,500
Emil Padua is being transferred
to police custody today.

92
00:04:54,500 --> 00:04:56,500
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

93
00:04:56,500 --> 00:04:59,767
I hope they catch
the others soon, too.

94
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:02,567
Including Greta Roja.

95
00:05:07,400 --> 00:05:09,700
I know Liam's
very hurt right now.

96
00:05:11,367 --> 00:05:13,633
He still loves
his mother very much.

97
00:05:13,633 --> 00:05:15,767
Any child would be hurt.

98
00:05:17,300 --> 00:05:18,633
More like shattered.

99
00:05:20,333 --> 00:05:22,700
We've known Ma'am Greta
for so long...

100
00:05:23,533 --> 00:05:24,967
She was always kind to us.

101
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:27,833
I never would've imagined
she was that kind of person.

102
00:05:28,833 --> 00:05:30,633
But a crime is still a crime.

103
00:05:31,967 --> 00:05:36,933
[STIRRING MUSIC SWELLS]

104
00:05:42,067 --> 00:05:43,833
[MUSIC FADES]

105
00:05:45,967 --> 00:05:47,467
Wendy...

106
00:05:49,733 --> 00:05:55,600
so many people got hurt
and suffered because of me.

107
00:05:55,600 --> 00:05:57,633
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

108
00:05:57,633 --> 00:05:58,767
Including you...

109
00:06:00,467 --> 00:06:01,633
Chief Ben...

110
00:06:02,900 --> 00:06:04,467
and Olsen.

111
00:06:05,767 --> 00:06:06,767
[SOBS]

112
00:06:06,767 --> 00:06:10,900
I don't know if you
can still believe me.

113
00:06:12,433 --> 00:06:13,567
But...

114
00:06:15,533 --> 00:06:18,467
I'm sorry for everything
I've done to you.

115
00:06:18,467 --> 00:06:21,867
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

116
00:06:21,867 --> 00:06:25,367
I don't know if I can
still believe you, Greta.

117
00:06:29,767 --> 00:06:32,467
[EMIL]<i> When Jacinto and I
</i> were planning this,

118
00:06:32,467 --> 00:06:37,767
<i>he told me to just scare
the hostages</i>

119
00:06:37,767 --> 00:06:42,100
<i>and not hurt anyone
except for one person.</i>

120
00:06:43,067 --> 00:06:45,867
<i>Then, he showed me
your picture.</i>

121
00:06:46,867 --> 00:06:49,567
<i>That's when I found out
about your background.</i>

122
00:06:49,567 --> 00:06:52,800
<i>You can't hurt anyone
except for me?</i>

123
00:06:53,500 --> 00:06:55,600
<i>Sounds like Jacinto
has a big grudge against you.</i>

124
00:06:56,067 --> 00:06:57,167
<i> I don't know him!</i>

125
00:06:57,167 --> 00:06:59,933
<i>Then why would he
single you out?</i>

126
00:06:59,933 --> 00:07:04,167
<i>Looks like someone has
a big grudge against your ex.</i>

127
00:07:04,167 --> 00:07:06,567
<i> Someone connected to Jacinto.</i>

128
00:07:06,567 --> 00:07:08,733
<i> And whoever that is...</i>

129
00:07:10,467 --> 00:07:14,900
<i>was probably involved
in planning this whole mess.</i>

130
00:07:15,667 --> 00:07:17,833
<i>Mrs. Greta Roja,
you need to come with us.</i>

131
00:07:19,133 --> 00:07:20,100
<i> Why?</i>

132
00:07:20,767 --> 00:07:23,067
<i> Why? What's going on?</i>

133
00:07:23,067 --> 00:07:24,933
<i>You've been named
as the mastermind</i>

134
00:07:24,933 --> 00:07:26,900
<i>behind the hostage-taking
at La Playa Roja.</i>

135
00:07:26,900 --> 00:07:28,133
<i> That's not true.</i>

136
00:07:28,133 --> 00:07:29,133
<i> We have evidence.</i>

137
00:07:29,133 --> 00:07:30,700
[JERICHO] Don't worry.

138
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:34,000
<i>- After the hostage-taking...
- No! That's a lie!</i>

139
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:36,133
<i>- I'll give you your share.
- It's all over the news.</i>

140
00:07:36,933 --> 00:07:38,533
[JERICHO]<i> You'll earn
</i> ten times as much.

141
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:43,167
I just don't understand

142
00:07:46,033 --> 00:07:48,433
why you've wanted me gone
for a long time.

143
00:07:48,467 --> 00:07:51,567
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

144
00:07:51,567 --> 00:07:55,100
You even ordered them
to not hurt anyone...

145
00:07:55,967 --> 00:07:57,633
except for me.

146
00:08:01,033 --> 00:08:02,167
Why?

147
00:08:10,067 --> 00:08:11,567
It wasn't out of anger.

148
00:08:13,133 --> 00:08:15,100
It was because I was afraid.

149
00:08:17,300 --> 00:08:21,300
I know Magnus still loves you.

150
00:08:23,333 --> 00:08:27,167
You're my real rival.

151
00:08:30,133 --> 00:08:31,667
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

152
00:08:37,467 --> 00:08:38,433
<i> Uh...</i>

153
00:08:43,733 --> 00:08:46,467
When I caught you...

154
00:08:47,667 --> 00:08:49,467
I kept everything to myself.

155
00:08:50,467 --> 00:08:52,067
I didn't confront you.

156
00:08:53,500 --> 00:08:54,700
Because I was scared...

157
00:08:56,500 --> 00:08:58,400
that he might choose you.

158
00:08:58,400 --> 00:09:01,433
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

159
00:09:01,433 --> 00:09:04,800
So when I had the opportunity
to get back at you,

160
00:09:06,700 --> 00:09:08,633
I pinned my case on you.

161
00:09:10,333 --> 00:09:12,067
I let you go to prison.

162
00:09:13,400 --> 00:09:16,367
Because I didn't want
to lose Magnus.

163
00:09:18,100 --> 00:09:19,500
I admit...

164
00:09:23,533 --> 00:09:25,200
I made a mistake.

165
00:09:26,800 --> 00:09:30,633
Magnus and I had a relationship
while you were married.

166
00:09:33,767 --> 00:09:35,767
But I distanced myself
afterward.

167
00:09:38,667 --> 00:09:39,867
You distanced yourself...

168
00:09:42,433 --> 00:09:45,100
but you stayed
with my husband.

169
00:09:46,900 --> 00:09:48,200
[VOICE BREAKS] Here.

170
00:09:48,200 --> 00:09:54,167
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

171
00:09:54,167 --> 00:09:59,667
<i>I know you were the one who
arranged for Wendy's release.</i>

172
00:10:00,433 --> 00:10:02,533
<i> She was sentenced to 15 years.</i>

173
00:10:03,300 --> 00:10:04,600
<i>But it was reduced
to 10 years.</i>

174
00:10:05,533 --> 00:10:08,333
<i>Someone arranged for that,
and it was you.</i>

175
00:10:09,333 --> 00:10:12,467
<i>You spent millions
to set Wendy free.</i>

176
00:10:12,933 --> 00:10:15,400
<i> Yes. Millions.</i>

177
00:10:16,167 --> 00:10:17,367
<i> My own money.</i>

178
00:10:18,267 --> 00:10:19,800
<i> It is not the company's money.</i>

179
00:10:20,767 --> 00:10:23,167
<i> And Wendy going to prison?</i>

180
00:10:23,167 --> 00:10:26,800
<i>That was all on you,
wasn't it, Greta?</i>

181
00:10:26,800 --> 00:10:30,833
<i>Because you took advantage
of Wendy's weakness.</i>

182
00:10:31,667 --> 00:10:32,867
Did you know?

183
00:10:33,733 --> 00:10:36,800
He was the one who
arranged for your release.

184
00:10:36,833 --> 00:10:43,633
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

185
00:10:58,333 --> 00:11:05,200
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

186
00:11:16,467 --> 00:11:21,300
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

187
00:11:21,300 --> 00:11:22,267
[EMIL GRUNTS]

188
00:11:31,600 --> 00:11:37,300
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

189
00:11:37,300 --> 00:11:38,367
[GROANS]

190
00:11:47,333 --> 00:11:48,433
[SCOFFS]

191
00:11:49,567 --> 00:11:50,633
How have you been?

192
00:11:52,467 --> 00:11:53,667
So, you're still alive.

193
00:11:55,533 --> 00:11:56,667
We're still alive.

194
00:11:58,500 --> 00:12:00,033
We're so lucky, aren't we?

195
00:12:00,033 --> 00:12:05,033
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

196
00:12:05,033 --> 00:12:06,333
[GRUNTS]

197
00:12:07,600 --> 00:12:08,700
[EMIL GRUNTS]

198
00:12:11,500 --> 00:12:14,567
General Cabral and I
had a deal.

199
00:12:14,600 --> 00:12:16,433
He promised he'd protect me.

200
00:12:17,033 --> 00:12:19,700
So why are you sending me
to prison with this demon?

201
00:12:19,700 --> 00:12:20,800
Demon?

202
00:12:21,733 --> 00:12:23,833
You're no different
from him, Jacinto.

203
00:12:23,833 --> 00:12:25,433
This isn't what we agreed on.

204
00:12:26,367 --> 00:12:28,000
You have an obligation to me!

205
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:30,033
Obligation?

206
00:12:30,800 --> 00:12:32,400
You're a cop.

207
00:12:32,400 --> 00:12:34,833
You swore an oath,
but what did you do?

208
00:12:35,767 --> 00:12:41,767
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

209
00:12:41,767 --> 00:12:43,900
Men, let's go!

210
00:12:53,833 --> 00:12:58,033
[ENGINES REVVING]

211
00:13:02,400 --> 00:13:09,333
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

212
00:13:17,433 --> 00:13:19,133
[UNSETTLING MUSIC SWELLS]

213
00:13:27,800 --> 00:13:32,500
[LINE RINGING]

214
00:13:35,600 --> 00:13:37,000
- [LINE DISCONNECTING]
- [OLSEN] Tch.

215
00:13:41,367 --> 00:13:43,433
Can we not turn in Mama yet?

216
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:48,400
- We had a deal, dude--
- I know.

217
00:13:48,400 --> 00:13:49,967
[LIAM BREATHES DEEPLY]

218
00:13:51,867 --> 00:13:54,667
Let me prepare a meal
for her first.

219
00:13:54,700 --> 00:13:56,800
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

220
00:13:56,800 --> 00:13:58,933
The charges she'll be facing
are serious.

221
00:14:00,533 --> 00:14:02,133
She'll be in prison
for a long time.

222
00:14:05,067 --> 00:14:07,400
I want to do this for her
before she goes.

223
00:14:12,033 --> 00:14:14,600
[LIAM]<i> I think
</i> what you did was wrong.

224
00:14:15,133 --> 00:14:17,633
<i>It was definitely wrong.
But, Ma...</i>

225
00:14:20,100 --> 00:14:22,133
<i>I can't stay mad at you
for long.</i>

226
00:14:25,033 --> 00:14:27,033
<i> No matter what you do...</i>

227
00:14:30,967 --> 00:14:32,533
<i> I love you very much.</i>

228
00:14:37,633 --> 00:14:39,400
<i>- What?
- Uh...</i>

229
00:14:39,867 --> 00:14:41,667
<i> I love you too, son.</i>

230
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:44,100
I admit...

231
00:14:46,100 --> 00:14:47,800
I already suspected...

232
00:14:50,733 --> 00:14:52,567
that Mama was behind everything.

233
00:14:56,567 --> 00:14:58,533
But I didn't say anything.

234
00:15:01,667 --> 00:15:03,100
I mean, how can I even accept

235
00:15:04,167 --> 00:15:06,667
that my own mother is the
mastermind behind everything?

236
00:15:06,667 --> 00:15:10,833
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

237
00:15:10,833 --> 00:15:13,000
Though I've been with her
all my life,

238
00:15:15,867 --> 00:15:17,667
I still don't know her well.

239
00:15:18,500 --> 00:15:19,567
[PUFFS]

240
00:15:21,133 --> 00:15:22,133
It hurts.

241
00:15:22,800 --> 00:15:23,967
It's confusing.

242
00:15:23,967 --> 00:15:26,833
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

243
00:15:26,833 --> 00:15:28,800
But one thing is clear to me.

244
00:15:30,833 --> 00:15:32,533
She's still my mother.

245
00:15:34,800 --> 00:15:36,700
I still love her.

246
00:15:36,700 --> 00:15:37,900
[OLSEN SCOFFS]

247
00:15:37,900 --> 00:15:39,067
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

248
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:41,767
I understand you, bro.

249
00:15:43,833 --> 00:15:45,833
I felt the same with my mother.

250
00:15:47,500 --> 00:15:48,800
[OLSEN] She lied to me.

251
00:15:49,167 --> 00:15:50,200
For a few times.

252
00:15:52,133 --> 00:15:53,633
But you're right.

253
00:15:53,633 --> 00:15:56,567
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

254
00:15:56,567 --> 00:15:58,033
I love her so much.

255
00:16:00,933 --> 00:16:03,600
So I forgave her, over and over.

256
00:16:07,067 --> 00:16:08,533
But, dude...

257
00:16:10,133 --> 00:16:11,833
I'm sorry, but...

258
00:16:12,700 --> 00:16:15,067
Your mom's lies are different.

259
00:16:16,633 --> 00:16:18,233
A lot of people died, Liam.

260
00:16:19,200 --> 00:16:20,567
I know.

261
00:16:20,567 --> 00:16:23,167
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

262
00:16:23,167 --> 00:16:25,800
But can you give me
some time to be with her?

263
00:16:28,867 --> 00:16:30,167
Just for the last time.

264
00:16:33,200 --> 00:16:35,200
It'll be our last meal together.

265
00:16:36,967 --> 00:16:41,233
Me, Mama, and Papa.

266
00:16:41,233 --> 00:16:48,167
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

267
00:17:00,033 --> 00:17:01,300
[BED THUDS SOFTLY]

268
00:17:08,133 --> 00:17:09,267
Greta.

269
00:17:10,867 --> 00:17:12,900
I want to tell you that...

270
00:17:15,933 --> 00:17:19,100
I promise to honor my vow to you
as your husband.

271
00:17:19,100 --> 00:17:21,833
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

272
00:17:21,833 --> 00:17:23,833
I will stay by your side.

273
00:17:25,067 --> 00:17:26,800
Until the end.

274
00:17:27,600 --> 00:17:28,667
[SCOFFS]

275
00:17:29,100 --> 00:17:30,633
Stay by my side?

276
00:17:32,067 --> 00:17:33,033
How?

277
00:17:34,033 --> 00:17:35,600
I'm going to jail.

278
00:17:35,600 --> 00:17:38,733
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

279
00:17:38,733 --> 00:17:40,767
You shouldn't be the only one
responsible.

280
00:17:41,967 --> 00:17:43,267
What do you mean?

281
00:17:46,133 --> 00:17:47,200
I know.

282
00:17:48,733 --> 00:17:51,400
I know that I need
to be jailed too.

283
00:17:51,400 --> 00:17:57,633
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

284
00:17:57,633 --> 00:17:58,600
No.

285
00:17:59,167 --> 00:18:00,767
You can't go to jail.

286
00:18:01,767 --> 00:18:03,033
For Liam's sake.

287
00:18:04,667 --> 00:18:06,267
More than your commitment to me

288
00:18:07,767 --> 00:18:10,167
is your commitment to our son.

289
00:18:11,633 --> 00:18:12,933
That's what you should think
about.

290
00:18:13,900 --> 00:18:15,033
[DOOR OPENS]

291
00:18:15,033 --> 00:18:16,067
Ma.

292
00:18:22,233 --> 00:18:23,333
Son.

293
00:18:25,033 --> 00:18:26,333
I'm ready.

294
00:18:26,333 --> 00:18:33,267
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

295
00:18:36,667 --> 00:18:41,733
[CAR ENGINES REVVING]

296
00:18:41,733 --> 00:18:48,667
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

297
00:19:03,500 --> 00:19:08,700
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

298
00:19:08,700 --> 00:19:12,733
[SUSPENSEFUL STING]

299
00:19:14,933 --> 00:19:18,467
<i>Your grandmother
is an excellent cook too.</i>

300
00:19:18,467 --> 00:19:20,933
<i> Good thing you take after her.</i>

301
00:19:20,933 --> 00:19:23,700
<i>I looked down on your passion
for cooking</i>

302
00:19:23,700 --> 00:19:26,333
<i> but this is to die for.</i>

303
00:19:26,333 --> 00:19:28,533
<i> And I promise from here on in</i>

304
00:19:28,567 --> 00:19:31,300
<i>that I will support
your passion.</i>

305
00:19:32,367 --> 00:19:34,300
<i>I'll bring La Playa Roja
back to life.</i>

306
00:19:34,300 --> 00:19:36,567
<i>I will open a new restaurant
at the resort.</i>

307
00:19:36,567 --> 00:19:38,633
<i>Olsen and I have a lot
of good memories there.</i>

308
00:19:38,633 --> 00:19:39,833
<i> A lot of mischief, you mean?</i>

309
00:19:39,833 --> 00:19:41,800
[OLSEN AND LIAM LAUGHING]

310
00:19:41,800 --> 00:19:44,000
<i> The women were disrespected!</i>

311
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:46,300
<i>Of course I saw them
having a hard time,</i>

312
00:19:46,300 --> 00:19:47,333
<i> I had to do something!</i>

313
00:19:47,333 --> 00:19:49,900
<i>And most of all, we have
each other's back!</i>

314
00:19:50,533 --> 00:19:52,633
<i>- Cheers!
- For the Roja family.</i>

315
00:19:53,367 --> 00:19:55,767
<i>Let's see if you can get
through this.</i>

316
00:19:55,767 --> 00:19:57,333
[TIRES SCREECH]

317
00:19:57,333 --> 00:19:58,400
<i> It's an ambush!</i>

318
00:19:59,033 --> 00:20:00,433
[SMOKE BOMB HISSING]

319
00:20:00,433 --> 00:20:06,467
- [RAPID GUNFIRE]
- [BULLETS CLANGING]

320
00:20:06,500 --> 00:20:13,067
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]
